INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the State Department of Health to study and to regulate the exposure of nurses to toxic substances.
EventItemMatterName: Department of Health to study and to regulate the exposure of nurses to toxic substances.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to permitting senior citizens residing in multiple dwellings the right to maintain pets in such dwellings.
EventItemMatterName: Permitting senior citizens residing in multiple dwellings the right to maintain pets in such dwellings.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to school recycling.
EventItemMatterName: School Recycling

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the Department of Education and the Department of Sanitation to immediately implement school recycling programs in all New York City public and private schools.
EventItemMatterName: DOE and the Dept of Sanitation to immediately implement school recycling programs in all NYC public and private schools.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to training building inspectors.
EventItemMatterName: Training building inspectors.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the department of buildings to post on its website the number of fatalities and accidents at construction sites.
EventItemMatterName: Department of buildings to report the number of fatalities and accidents at construction sites.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Youth Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to pass the Summer Jobs Stimulus Act of 2008.
EventItemMatterName: Congress to pass the Summer Jobs Stimulus Act of 2008.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to reducing greenhouse gas emissions and the repeal of local law number 55 for the year 2007.
EventItemMatterName: Reducing greenhouse gas emissions and the repeal of local law number 55 for the year 2007.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: Resolution finding that the enactment of Preconsidered Int. No. 756 does not have a significant adverse impact on the environment and is consistent with The State Environmental Quality Review Act.
EventItemMatterName: Enactment of Preconsidered Int. No. 756 does not have a significant adverse impact on the environment and is consistent with The State Environmental Quality Review Act.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring usage of fully shielded light fixtures.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring usage of fully shielded light fixtures.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass bill S 7000, which requires the State Department of Health to implement a permit process for exhibitors commercially displaying human remains.
EventItemMatterName: State Department of Health to implement a permit process for exhibitors commercially displaying human remains.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to creating and disseminating a best practices at construction sites within the city of New York manual.
EventItemMatterName: Creating and disseminating a best practices at construction sites within the city of New York manual.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to creating a construction industry whistleblower hotline within the New York City department of buildings.
EventItemMatterName: Creating a construction industry whistleblower hotline within the New York City department of buildings.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Department of Health to study the effects of fluoride in tap water.
EventItemMatterName: Department of Health to study the effects of fluoride in tap water.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the appointment of a safety compliance officer with respect to construction sites.
EventItemMatterName: The appointment of an independent monitor with respect to construction sites.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the City of New York, in relation to the posting of signs at construction sites.
EventItemMatterName: Posting of signs at construction sites.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution denouncing the continued violence in Colombia and calling upon all parties to cease all violent attacks against civilians and respect their human rights.
EventItemMatterName: Denouncing the continued violence in Colombia and calling upon insurgent armies to cease all violent attacks against civilians and respect their human rights.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Small Business
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to small business regulatory flexibility.
EventItemMatterName: Small business regulatory flexibility.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York in relation to classifying housekeeping violations as immediately hazardous, certifying correction of immediately hazardous housekeeping violations, adding civil penalties for violations of stop work orders.
EventItemMatterName: Classifying housekeeping violations as immediately hazardous.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring owners of construction sites to clean graffiti from the construction site and any construction-related materials at no cost to the city of New York.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring owners of construction sites to clean graffiti from the construction site and any construction-related materials at no cost to NYC.
